    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-07T01:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-07T01:54:00-05:00" n="919"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d919">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-07T10:00:00+03:06"
                            >July 7, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. My 55, June 22, 5 p.m. Number of pilgrims to Mecca this year is estimated as
                    high as 50,000. Substantial numbers should begin arriving by end September and
                    rush will begin a month later.</p>
                <pb facs="0885" n="873" xml:id="pg_873"/>
                <p>All 15 million riyals referred to in Cairo’s 861, May 11, 9 a.m. will be needed
                    to combat upward tendency of riyal resulting from receipt of promised gold and
                    influx of foreign currencies with pilgrims. A runaway riyal will cause
                    destitution among pilgrims and otherwise aggravate difficulties of local
                    government.</p>
                <p>Long range plan mentioned in Department’s 27, June 30, 1 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >10</hi>] p.m.<note n="71" xml:id="d919fn71">Not printed; it was a private
                        telegram between officials of the California Arabian Standard Oil Company
                        (Casoc) containing information as to the Department’s interest and efforts
                        in the direction of solving on a long-range basis the Saudi Arabian fiscal
                        problem by means of a plan of currency stabilization (012.3/9605a).</note>
                    should not be permitted to distract attention from urgency of present needs.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Cairo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
